WEBVTT

00:00.900 --> 00:02.197
<i>Previously on Ugly Betty...</i>

00:02.235 --> 00:03.634
Oh, no, no.

00:04.104 --> 00:06.368
You are not the same person
I met three years ago.

00:06.406 --> 00:10.740
Betty, you've already changed,
but you're still you.

00:10.977 --> 00:13.411
- I'm an editor now.
- Really?

00:13.446 --> 00:15.971
I don't want you ever
around my mother again!

00:16.015 --> 00:17.244
What the hell is going on?

00:17.283 --> 00:20.411
He's only interested in his career
and leeching off of you.

00:20.453 --> 00:23.013
- Tyler is not who you think he is.
- Who is he, then?

00:23.056 --> 00:24.751
He's your brother.

00:25.058 --> 00:26.821
I really need to see you tonight.

00:26.860 --> 00:28.521
I'm kind of busy right now.

00:28.561 --> 00:30.529
Thanks for not ditching me tonight.

00:30.563 --> 00:32.052
I could really use a friend.

00:32.098 --> 00:33.190
Well, you've got one.

00:33.233 --> 00:36.361
Hilda Suarez, I love you.
Will you marry me?

00:36.569 --> 00:37.763
Oh!

00:38.304 --> 00:41.398
- So, you like someone.
- Yeah.

00:41.441 --> 00:43.966
What is their name?

00:44.010 --> 00:45.238
Lily.

00:46.579 --> 00:48.274
I just got off the phone
with Lena Korvinka!

00:48.314 --> 00:51.909
She loved my audition and wants to
formally invite me to join her class!

00:54.054 --> 01:00.015
Romeo, Romeo!
Wherefore art thou Romeo?

01:00.393 --> 01:05.524
Deny thy father and refuse thy name...

01:08.101 --> 01:12.128
You see? Acting is reinvention.

01:12.172 --> 01:13.969
I mean, who is to say

01:14.007 --> 01:16.840
that Juliet has to be
the prettiest girl in the room?

01:16.876 --> 01:20.368
You know, maybe she's some
misguided boob with bad eyes

01:20.413 --> 01:23.905
and bad hair and bad teeth.

01:28.488 --> 01:31.480
- What?
- Okay, everybody take two minutes.

01:31.524 --> 01:35.358
I'm just gonna call my cat
and grab tonight's speaker.

01:35.862 --> 01:37.352
Am I too early to pick you up?

01:37.397 --> 01:39.194
Yeah, but you should stay
for the guest speaker.

01:39.232 --> 01:41.962
- He used to date a Gossip Girl.
- That's why he's speaking?

01:42.001 --> 01:45.698
- That's his qualification?
- That's all I need.

01:45.738 --> 01:48.400
Oh, Aunt Betty, this is my friend Austin.

01:48.441 --> 01:51.467
- Austin, hi.
- Hey.

01:51.511 --> 01:54.036
It's very nice to meet you.
I've heard so much about you.

01:54.080 --> 01:55.638
You tell her what a great actor I am?

01:55.682 --> 01:57.946
No, just what a giant ego you have.

01:57.984 --> 02:00.680
- And this is Lily.
- Hi. Cute glasses.

02:00.720 --> 02:02.847
Thanks. Nice to meet you.

02:04.124 --> 02:06.183
- That's the girl that I like.
Good news.

02:06.226 --> 02:09.491
Tinker Bell ate his dinner,
and he's going to be fine.

02:09.529 --> 02:14.933
All right, now, tonight's speaker
is an award-winning playwright

02:14.968 --> 02:18.267
and a foxy little muckety muck.

02:18.304 --> 02:22.468
<i>His latest play, The Rebirth of Rita,</i>

02:22.509 --> 02:24.238
opens next week.

02:24.277 --> 02:27.906
Please give a warm welcome
to Zachary Boule.

02:31.851 --> 02:33.216
I know him.

02:33.253 --> 02:37.883
I read his first play.
It was so good and so tragic.

02:37.924 --> 02:39.983
What a nice treat for me.

02:40.026 --> 02:41.960
Hey, everybody.

02:42.829 --> 02:44.319
Hi.

02:44.364 --> 02:47.492
So, Lena asked me
to speak about reinvention today,

02:47.534 --> 02:49.900
which is a theme in my next play.

02:50.803 --> 02:53.169
It was like he was talking directly to me.

02:53.206 --> 02:56.369
Everything he was saying
about reinventing yourself,

02:56.409 --> 02:58.343
your look, your life.

02:58.411 --> 03:01.278
Mmm. That's very interesting.

03:01.314 --> 03:03.782
I mean, that's everything
I've been doing this year.

03:03.816 --> 03:07.115
- My new look, my new job...
- You don't say.

03:07.153 --> 03:09.212
Hilda, stop.
I see your engagement ring, okay?

03:09.255 --> 03:10.882
Congratulations.

03:10.924 --> 03:13.017
Good, because I'm practicing
how to show it off

03:13.059 --> 03:15.755
without looking like I'm showing it off.

03:15.795 --> 03:19.526
- Do my hands look dry?
- Too obvious.

03:19.566 --> 03:23.024
As I was saying,
Zach was really inspiring.

03:23.069 --> 03:25.594
And by "inspiring," do you mean cute?

03:25.638 --> 03:26.866
- No.
- Yes, you do.

03:26.906 --> 03:29.704
That is not even what I was thinking.

03:29.742 --> 03:32.768
I mean, not that it would matter.
He dates Gossip Girls.

03:32.812 --> 03:36.407
And he won a Drama Desk Award.
I write a blog.

03:36.449 --> 03:37.643
I won a Blobby.

03:37.684 --> 03:41.085
<i>But I was thinking about pitching him
to Mode for the New York issue.</i>

03:41.120 --> 03:45.648
Yeah, you should.
Nothing says New York like theater.

03:45.692 --> 03:48.786
- Here, let me fix your hair.
- No. I see it.

03:49.996 --> 03:53.659
- You just scratched my glasses.
- That's because it's a diamond.

03:57.971 --> 04:00.906
- Hey. Your mom's on the phone.
- I don't want to talk to her.

04:00.940 --> 04:02.999
I can't keep telling her
you're in the bathroom.

04:03.042 --> 04:05.738
That's what you've been telling her
for four days?

04:05.778 --> 04:09.544
- Does she at least sound worried?
- Just talk to her.

04:09.582 --> 04:11.743
She waits 30 years
to tell me I have a brother.

04:11.784 --> 04:13.081
After she drops that bomb,

04:13.119 --> 04:15.417
she whisks him off to Paris
to meet Alexis.

04:15.455 --> 04:18.117
I think I'm entitled
to a little more time than that.

04:18.156 --> 04:21.820
- Think about how your brother feels.
- Don't call him my brother.

04:21.861 --> 04:25.024
- My only brother is my sister, Alexis.
- Exactly my point.

04:25.064 --> 04:28.431
The poor guy gets off a bus
from South Dakota, you punched him,

04:28.468 --> 04:32.495
and now he's whisked off
to meet Manzilla in some foreign land.

04:32.538 --> 04:34.870
Since when are you his friend?

04:34.907 --> 04:35.931
I'm not. I just...

04:37.110 --> 04:38.475
You know what? Forget it.
I have a lot of work

04:38.511 --> 04:39.535
I have to get back to.

04:39.579 --> 04:40.910
Daniel Meade's office.

04:40.947 --> 04:43.916
Now, Marc, I need all thoughts
of go-go boys in glitter pants

04:43.950 --> 04:45.247
out of your head today.

04:45.285 --> 04:46.809
James Cameron's people
are gonna call.

04:46.853 --> 04:49.481
They're doing the CGI work
to help me recreate old New York

04:49.522 --> 04:51.114
- for my cover shoot.
- Right. I should tell you

04:51.157 --> 04:54.718
- Daniel's concerned about the cost.
- I don't care about Daniel.

04:54.761 --> 04:56.558
You spend money to make money.

04:56.963 --> 04:58.521
Good morning.

05:00.967 --> 05:04.368
Was that monochromatic blur
Betty Suarez?

05:04.404 --> 05:09.000
I know. Where are the polka dots
and butterflies and Mexican blankets?

05:09.742 --> 05:10.800
Yeah.

05:10.843 --> 05:14.745
- Does she look nice?
- Willie,

05:15.248 --> 05:20.481
you swore you'd die before you ever
complimented a Suarez ensemble.

05:22.288 --> 05:24.017
- Oh, my God.
Willie!

05:24.057 --> 05:26.150
- What happened?
- Isn't it obvious?

05:26.192 --> 05:29.093
Your stumble into good taste
has killed her.

05:30.096 --> 05:32.064
By now you've all heard
what happened to Wilhelmina.

05:32.098 --> 05:34.692
She is having surgery
on a perforated ulcer,

05:34.734 --> 05:36.861
but she is going to live.

05:36.903 --> 05:40.430
The good news is I am taking point
on the New York issue.

05:40.473 --> 05:42.998
So I guess
we should send flowers or something.

05:43.042 --> 05:45.738
I guess $40 should about cover it,
don't you think?

05:45.778 --> 05:48.474
<i>It's just like you to cheap out, Daniel.</i>

05:48.514 --> 05:50.641
<i>- What the hell are you...
- I have a little time before surgery,</i>

05:50.683 --> 05:52.480
<i>so I'm gonna run this meeting,
thank you.</i>

05:52.518 --> 05:54.748
Do you really think that's the best idea?

05:54.787 --> 05:56.721
<i>Daniel, I could die on the table.</i>

05:56.756 --> 05:58.417
<i>Are you really gonna
take this away from me?</i>

05:58.458 --> 06:01.325
<i>- I thought it was a routine...
- Features, what do you got for me?</i>

06:01.861 --> 06:04.728
Hi, Wilhelmina, it's Betty.

06:04.764 --> 06:07.858
I've been thinking
about the idea of reinvention

06:07.900 --> 06:10.698
and how people
come to New York City to...

06:12.138 --> 06:14.868
<i>- Oh, my God, are you okay?
- I'm fine.</i>

06:14.907 --> 06:17.068
<i>It's your pitch. It's excruciating.</i>

06:17.110 --> 06:21.240
<i>- Just give her a chance.
- Fine. Five words. Go.</i>

06:21.848 --> 06:22.872
Um...

06:25.251 --> 06:26.548
Profile.

06:27.053 --> 06:28.247
Um...

06:28.554 --> 06:30.283
Playwright.

06:30.323 --> 06:32.257
<i>- Reinvention.
- No.</i>

06:32.291 --> 06:35.590
<i>I gave you five words.
You chose to use "um" twice.</i>

06:35.628 --> 06:39.325
<i>No playwrights.
Theater is dead, and so is your pitch.</i>

06:40.133 --> 06:42.124
<i>I am not wearing that.</i>

06:44.504 --> 06:47.996
<i>Apparently my table is ready,
so I will leave you with this.</i>

06:48.040 --> 06:51.601
<i>I've given Marc detailed instructions
as to how to proceed</i>

06:51.644 --> 06:53.475
<i>with my New Amsterdam shoot.</i>

06:53.513 --> 06:56.710
Wilhelmina, that's too expensive.
I told you we are not doing that.

06:56.749 --> 06:58.273
<i>Daniel, you stupid...</i>

07:00.653 --> 07:02.985
All right, that shoot is canceled.

07:03.523 --> 07:06.117
Daniel, can I please
re-pitch you my idea?

07:06.159 --> 07:09.026
Look, I hate to say it, but I have
to agree with Wilhelmina on this one.

07:09.061 --> 07:11.461
I don't see how it fits
in a fashion magazine.

07:11.497 --> 07:14.295
It does. Look at how fashionable he is.

07:14.333 --> 07:16.824
Besides, his new play
is all about reinvention,

07:16.869 --> 07:18.359
which is the core of fashion, right?

07:18.404 --> 07:20.804
I mean,
what's out yesterday is in tomorrow.

07:20.840 --> 07:24.537
And I'm sorry, but New York is theater.
I don't care what Wilhelmina says.

07:24.577 --> 07:27.444
- Is he with Leighton Meester?
- They're not together anymore.

07:27.480 --> 07:29.277
Wow, you said that fast.

07:29.315 --> 07:31.715
You know what? If you want
to ask him out, just ask him out.

07:31.751 --> 07:33.946
- You don't have to do a story on him.
- What?

07:33.986 --> 07:37.251
No, that has nothing to do with it.

07:37.290 --> 07:40.623
I just think that this would be
a really good story.

07:40.960 --> 07:44.555
Run with it. At the very least,
it will piss off Wilhelmina.

07:44.597 --> 07:49.364
Thank you. And trust me,
this is totally professional.

07:52.438 --> 07:56.499
- Your real name is Ezra Butinsky?
- Why would I make that up?

07:56.542 --> 08:01.172
I guess it doesn't have quite the same
romantic ring as "Zachary Boule. "

08:01.214 --> 08:05.275
So you think my name's romantic?
Is this interview taking a turn?

08:07.320 --> 08:10.619
Sorry, I interrupted you before.
What was your question?

08:10.656 --> 08:14.922
Right, 'cause I was
asking you a question.

08:15.361 --> 08:19.764
How has your time at Oxford
influenced your new play,

08:19.799 --> 08:21.596
<i>The Rebirth of Rita?</i>

08:22.301 --> 08:26.704
Off the record, I kind of embellished
my bio to sound more interesting.

08:26.739 --> 08:29.264
- Oh.
- I did one summer program there.

08:29.308 --> 08:32.106
The truth is I grew up in New Jersey.

08:32.144 --> 08:35.010
Typical dork, glasses and braces.

08:35.481 --> 08:39.144
Not that I'm implying that glasses
and braces make you a dork.

08:39.184 --> 08:42.211
- It's just... I mean, I still...
- It's okay, I can handle "dork. "

08:42.255 --> 08:44.155
I'm supposed to be
getting them off soon anyway.

08:44.190 --> 08:47.557
I just have to find a new orthodontist
because my old one went crazy on me.

08:47.593 --> 08:50.619
I love mine.
I can get you the info, if you want.

08:50.663 --> 08:52.426
- Yeah, that would be great.
- Although,

08:52.465 --> 08:54.592
somehow those work for you.

08:54.634 --> 08:55.896
Thanks.

08:56.636 --> 09:01.835
Okay, so, what about writing
do you enjoy the most?

09:01.874 --> 09:06.072
I'm kind of an over-thinker,
so I like to create impulsive characters.

09:06.112 --> 09:09.707
You know, the kind that get swept up
in a moment and take action.

09:09.749 --> 09:13.776
- That sounds liberating.
- Doesn't it?

09:13.819 --> 09:15.787
I mean, wouldn't our lives be
so much more interesting

09:15.821 --> 09:18.016
if we didn't think
everything through first?

09:18.057 --> 09:20.582
- Totally.
- Lf we just lived in the moment.

09:20.626 --> 09:22.992
We want something, we go for it.

09:24.000 --> 09:30.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

09:52.024 --> 09:54.185
Oh, my God. I'm sorry.

09:54.226 --> 09:55.921
- No, it's okay.
- No, it's not okay.

09:55.962 --> 10:00.228
It's totally unprofessional
and disrespectful to you

10:00.266 --> 10:03.997
and whatever potential starlet girlfriend
you might have.

10:04.036 --> 10:05.731
I'm sorry.

10:05.771 --> 10:07.671
Look, I can assure you
that this will in no way

10:07.707 --> 10:10.835
negatively affect the piece
that I am writing on you. Sorry.

10:12.979 --> 10:15.777
- Good, you're still here.
- Hey, you.

10:15.815 --> 10:17.373
Sorry to bother.
I know you probably have

10:17.416 --> 10:21.182
- some big, fabulous date or something.
- You're sweet.

10:21.687 --> 10:24.383
But no, and now you've made me sad.

10:25.591 --> 10:26.956
What's up?

10:26.993 --> 10:29.860
My acting class is doing a scene night
for family and friends,

10:29.895 --> 10:31.726
- and I wanted to invite you.
- Oh.

10:32.965 --> 10:36.059
A night of scenes
performed by teenagers.

10:36.102 --> 10:38.730
How fun. How many scenes are there?

10:38.771 --> 10:41.035
- Twelve.
- And what number are you in the order?

10:41.073 --> 10:43.371
- Ten.
- Are any of these kids famous?

10:43.409 --> 10:46.276
One girl did a PSA for lead paint
when she was four.

10:46.312 --> 10:48.041
She had to chew a windowsill.

10:48.080 --> 10:49.104
Oh.

10:49.215 --> 10:51.206
It's Lily, the girl that I like.

10:51.250 --> 10:52.649
Right. So... So...

10:52.685 --> 10:56.815
- That's still happening?
- Yeah, it's great.

10:56.856 --> 11:01.793
- My friend Austin likes her, too.
- Okay, so, you both like her.

11:01.827 --> 11:03.055
Mmm-hmm.

11:03.963 --> 11:06.523
Well, count me in. I love drama.

11:08.334 --> 11:09.961
And I like theater.

11:13.406 --> 11:17.137
<i>Zachary Boule is one of
Broadway's brightest rising stars.</i>

11:17.443 --> 11:21.971
<i>In fact, I'd say the only thing brighter
is his dashing smile.</i>

11:22.014 --> 11:23.675
<i>Dashing smile?</i>

11:23.716 --> 11:25.149
<i>Keep it clean, Suarez.</i>

11:27.420 --> 11:30.412
<i>We met at a bar on 29th Street.</i>

11:30.456 --> 11:32.481
<i>His handshake was firm.</i>

11:32.525 --> 11:36.962
<i>I couldn't help but imagine those
same hands massaging my shoulders.</i>

11:40.900 --> 11:43.596
I need you to do something for me.

11:44.537 --> 11:47.404
Anything, Zach, anything at all.

11:47.440 --> 11:51.672
- I want to read my play to you.
- That's exactly what I hoped you'd say.

11:53.746 --> 11:56.840
"Page One. Act One. "

11:56.949 --> 11:58.473
That's amazing.

11:59.118 --> 12:03.987
"A spotlight illuminates
a well-worn easy chair, center stage. "

12:04.123 --> 12:06.353
An easy chair, that's so good.

12:11.764 --> 12:14.597
Wow, you're really in the zone, huh?

12:15.000 --> 12:18.436
Zone? Yes. I'm feeling the zone.

12:19.004 --> 12:21.598
- How was that thing last night?
- Thing?

12:22.007 --> 12:25.499
You mean my meeting with Zach?
Zachary. Zachary Boule.

12:25.811 --> 12:27.745
Good, but I wouldn't really
call it a "thing. "

12:27.780 --> 12:29.805
I'd call it an interview.

12:30.082 --> 12:33.347
Wow. You're being kind of weird.

12:33.385 --> 12:36.149
I'm not acting weird.
You're acting weird.

12:36.756 --> 12:40.317
- Hello?
- Zachary. How weird.

12:42.061 --> 12:43.187
Um...

12:43.562 --> 12:46.793
- Daniel, this is Zachary.
- It's nice to meet you.

12:47.733 --> 12:50.861
You have a really big fan here.

12:50.903 --> 12:52.632
Daniel, I'm not a fan.

12:52.671 --> 12:55.663
I'm not a fan. I'm an impartial journalist.
Can I help you with something?

12:55.708 --> 12:58.370
Just wanted to follow up
on our thing last night.

12:58.410 --> 13:00.435
Called it a "thing. "

13:00.479 --> 13:03.004
Well, let's go somewhere and talk.

13:06.886 --> 13:10.083
All we have to do is drop these caftans
and turbans off with Wilhelmina,

13:10.122 --> 13:12.647
the outfit of choice
for any recovering diva.

13:12.691 --> 13:14.750
Tyler just sent me a text.

13:14.794 --> 13:17.729
He wants to have dinner with me
when he gets back from Paris.

13:17.763 --> 13:20.425
I can't decide if it's weird or hot

13:20.466 --> 13:23.765
that you're sleeping with one brother
and secretly befriending the other.

13:23.803 --> 13:26.966
I can't, either. On one hand,
I've known Daniel for years

13:27.006 --> 13:28.564
and I really care about him,

13:28.607 --> 13:32.543
but on the other hand, Tyler's a model,
so it's kind of even, right?

13:33.245 --> 13:34.473
Dilemmas.

13:34.513 --> 13:36.242
<i>Dr. Vine to proctology.</i>

13:36.282 --> 13:38.250
<i>Dr. Vine to proctology.</i>

13:40.653 --> 13:42.780
Sweet, she's napping.

13:42.822 --> 13:45.222
I want to pull back the covers
and look at her body while she sleeps.

13:45.257 --> 13:46.952
No, no, no, no.

13:46.992 --> 13:49.722
Let's just drop this stuff off,
go have a nice lunch.

13:49.762 --> 13:52.697
- I was thinking soup and half a salad.
- Okay.

13:55.601 --> 13:58.593
Really, Marc? Soup and half a salad?

13:58.637 --> 14:02.004
When the cat's away, the mice
will gorge themselves to death.

14:02.041 --> 14:06.501
Oh, my God.
Willie, you're in a semi-private room.

14:06.545 --> 14:08.069
This is all they had available.

14:08.113 --> 14:12.914
Lucky for me, she gets no visitors.
Just slowly rotting away.

14:13.252 --> 14:14.879
Oh, sad face.

14:15.621 --> 14:17.589
Well, you're looking awfully spry

14:17.623 --> 14:20.183
for someone who's recovering
from a perforated ulcer.

14:20.226 --> 14:21.853
Well, I have to stay alert

14:21.894 --> 14:25.352
to go over the final details
for our New Amsterdam shoot.

14:25.397 --> 14:26.523
Oh.

14:26.565 --> 14:30.797
Did you not remember
that Daniel killed that yesterday?

14:30.836 --> 14:33.396
Of course, I remembered,
and I'm reviving it.

14:33.439 --> 14:37.341
So we'll work from here.
And don't you dare tell Daniel.

14:38.210 --> 14:41.077
If you're hungry,
call down for some ice chips.

14:43.549 --> 14:46.245
I'm sorry that you had to come
all the way down here.

14:46.285 --> 14:48.116
Well, the way
we ended things last night...

14:48.153 --> 14:52.522
I know, Zach. I'm sorry.
I am so embarrassed.

14:52.558 --> 14:55.891
I wish I could take everything back.
I mean, I'm a journalist.

14:55.928 --> 14:58.419
I should be able to maintain
a certain level of...

15:04.270 --> 15:07.569
- Have dinner with me tonight.
- I would love to.

15:09.308 --> 15:14.575
No. No, I can't.
I pushed really hard to write this article,

15:14.813 --> 15:17.873
and if my boss found out
that you and I...

15:17.917 --> 15:20.715
That we're involved,
that would look really bad.

15:21.754 --> 15:25.155
So, then we won't tell him.

15:25.190 --> 15:28.956
If anyone found out...
Zach, you're in the tabloids.

15:28.994 --> 15:31.428
You date two actresses
and crash a motorcycle

15:31.463 --> 15:34.364
